WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:01.653
.

00:01.697 --> 00:03.525
[bright tones]

00:03.568 --> 00:05.440
- Previously,
on "Good Girls"...

00:05.483 --> 00:07.703
- Did you come to steal my baby
like you stole my husband?

00:07.746 --> 00:10.358
- We can do this.
Let's meet this little guy.

00:10.401 --> 00:12.577
- Are you in love with your ex?
- Kind of.

00:12.621 --> 00:14.362
- So do I even have
a shot here?

00:14.405 --> 00:15.450
[moaning]

00:15.493 --> 00:16.755
- How's it going
with the sister?

00:16.799 --> 00:18.018
- I'm out of the friend zone.

00:18.061 --> 00:19.671
- Already?
- Yeah.

00:19.715 --> 00:22.065
- You didn't tell him yet?
- Tell me what?

00:22.109 --> 00:25.025
- We're partners now.

00:25.068 --> 00:26.504
- What's homeboy look like?

00:26.548 --> 00:27.810
- That's him.

00:27.853 --> 00:30.334
- [gasping]
- Can you guys kill him or not?

00:30.378 --> 00:32.858
- Half up front,
the rest after we dust him.

00:32.902 --> 00:34.251
- Oh, my God!

00:34.295 --> 00:36.079
Oh, no, no, no!

00:36.123 --> 00:39.300
- First thing that you did
was to check on your money.

00:39.343 --> 00:42.172
- He left me,
and he took my kids.

00:42.216 --> 00:43.608
- It'll be worse for him

00:43.652 --> 00:45.175
when they find out he took
the pen cap.

00:45.219 --> 00:46.916
So you let me know
how you want to play it.

00:46.959 --> 00:50.006
- You took this from my house
while my daughter was missing.

00:50.050 --> 00:51.399
Are you gonna give it to him?

00:51.442 --> 00:52.443
- No.

00:52.487 --> 00:54.445
- I would never even
think about it.

00:54.489 --> 00:57.361
- Did you remove a pen cap
from the evidence locker?

00:57.405 --> 00:59.102
- I did not.
I failed.

00:59.146 --> 01:00.277
- Like, inconclusive or--

01:00.321 --> 01:02.105
- Capital "F".
Failed.

01:02.149 --> 01:03.759
Feds, they opened up
an IA deal or whatever.

01:03.802 --> 01:06.196
- I have literally no idea--
- Internal Affairs, okay?

01:06.240 --> 01:08.068
They investigate dirty cops.

01:08.111 --> 01:10.853
- You might want to pack up
an umbrella today.

01:10.896 --> 01:12.376
- I'm done.

01:12.420 --> 01:13.595
- You quit?
- You get them up.

01:13.638 --> 01:15.292
I'm so over it.
- [laughs]

01:15.336 --> 01:16.728
You pull the covers off?

01:16.772 --> 01:19.557
- "Covers"?
I threw water in their faces.

01:19.601 --> 01:21.733
There's a full-on
insubordination at this point.

01:21.777 --> 01:23.561
And then when we're
30 minutes late for drop-off,

01:23.605 --> 01:25.172
who's gonna get the call?
- You get the call.

01:25.215 --> 01:28.784
- I get the call.
- All right, I got this.

01:30.568 --> 01:31.787
Drink that.

01:31.830 --> 01:33.310
- Thank you.

01:33.354 --> 01:36.096
[TV plays indistinctly]

01:36.139 --> 01:39.099
[playing Bach's
Toccata and Fugue]

01:39.142 --> 01:41.927
[eerie music continues]

01:41.971 --> 01:44.930
- Oh, that's nasty.
- Right?

01:44.974 --> 01:46.410
- [laughs]

01:46.454 --> 01:47.585
- Daddy!

01:47.629 --> 01:50.240
- Stop it, Daddy!

01:50.284 --> 01:51.981
- You're gonna
give us nightmares.

01:52.024 --> 01:53.113
- Then don't be sleeping.

01:53.156 --> 01:54.549
- Okay, cereal's on the table.

01:54.592 --> 01:56.725
- I want hotcakes.
- Hotcakes?

01:56.768 --> 01:58.248
You must still be dreaming
if you think

01:58.292 --> 01:59.467
you're gonna get hotcakes.
[knocking]

01:59.510 --> 02:01.251
- You expecting somebody?

02:01.295 --> 02:04.124
- No.
- Hmm.

02:04.167 --> 02:06.169
- You need a haircut, buddy.

02:07.214 --> 02:08.606
- Morning.

02:08.650 --> 02:10.260
Morning, all.

02:10.304 --> 02:12.349
Mind if we come in?
- What's going on?

02:12.393 --> 02:15.613
What's up, Mike?
- You guys go get dressed.

02:28.191 --> 02:30.411
- What's happening?

02:31.847 --> 02:36.156
- You mind if we not do this
in front of them?

02:36.199 --> 02:37.722
- I need you
to turn around, buddy.

02:37.766 --> 02:39.985
- Let's just talk
about this, okay?

02:40.029 --> 02:41.639
- Mm-mm, been there, done that.

02:41.683 --> 02:43.554
- You have the right
to remain silent.

02:43.598 --> 02:45.904
- I know the drill, Mike.
- Go to your rooms.

02:45.948 --> 02:47.558
- Hey, hey, listen.

02:47.602 --> 02:49.604
Listen to your mommy, okay?
Daddy's gonna be fine, okay?

02:49.647 --> 02:53.173
You go to school and I'm gonna
call you when I can, okay?

02:53.216 --> 02:56.915
[both mouthing words]

03:03.095 --> 03:05.489
- This didn't have to happen.

03:10.755 --> 03:12.322
[door shuts]

03:12.366 --> 03:14.542
- [inhales shakily]

03:16.631 --> 03:20.025
[children laughing distantly]

03:20.069 --> 03:23.681
[woman singing
in foreign language]

03:23.725 --> 03:27.163
[children repeating singing
in foreign language]

03:27.207 --> 03:28.860
♪

03:28.904 --> 03:32.429
[children yelling]

03:32.473 --> 03:39.741
♪

03:40.872 --> 03:43.353
- Hey, Mommy!
- We're making panca--

03:43.397 --> 03:45.790
[music, voices stop]

03:49.577 --> 03:51.274
- You can't just
take them away.

03:51.318 --> 03:52.971
- Is this where you meet?

03:53.015 --> 03:54.756
- Who says that?

03:54.799 --> 03:57.715
- "Mommy's friend with
the drawings on his neck."

03:57.759 --> 04:00.240
[children chattering,
laughing]

04:00.283 --> 04:01.850
- I keep them far away.

04:01.893 --> 04:05.332
- Jane says he's got
a little boy about her age.

04:06.594 --> 04:07.899
- What do you want?

04:07.943 --> 04:09.161
- I want you done.

04:09.205 --> 04:10.424
- It's not that simple.

04:10.467 --> 04:12.382
- I want my family safe.

04:12.426 --> 04:14.384
- How do you think
we pay for things?

04:14.428 --> 04:15.994
- Who cares?
- We could lose our house.

04:16.038 --> 04:18.258
- So we'll get an apartment.
- With four children?

04:18.301 --> 04:19.476
- Probably sleep better.

04:19.520 --> 04:21.130
- It's not just
the house, Dean.

04:21.173 --> 04:22.436
It's braces, it's college,

04:22.479 --> 04:23.741
it's the clothes
on their backs.

04:23.785 --> 04:26.266
- At least the park
would be a park again.

04:32.184 --> 04:34.970
- Wait!
Will you just wait?

04:39.627 --> 04:42.804
- What about Emma's birthday?

04:44.458 --> 04:47.330
- We're doing it at my mom's.

04:47.374 --> 04:50.768
Kids would love to see you.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.990
[knocking on door]

04:55.033 --> 04:57.819
[TV plays indistinctly]

04:58.646 --> 05:00.996
- Pajamas?
It's almost lunch.

05:01.039 --> 05:04.173
- Gee, thanks for the update,
Father Time.

05:04.216 --> 05:05.305
Excuse me.

05:05.348 --> 05:07.350
- Hey.

05:07.394 --> 05:09.265
- Great, come on in.

05:09.309 --> 05:12.137
- Um...

05:12.181 --> 05:13.965
I just wanted to say thank you

05:14.009 --> 05:17.491
for delivering my son.

05:18.622 --> 05:21.538
- Starbucks.
You shouldn't have.

05:21.582 --> 05:23.714
- Look, it'd be weird
if I got you, like,

05:23.758 --> 05:26.369
a tennis bracelet
or a massage or--

05:26.413 --> 05:28.197
I just didn't want
to be creepy.

05:28.240 --> 05:30.286
- So you went with what you get

05:30.330 --> 05:31.461
your postman on Christmas.

05:31.505 --> 05:33.028
- Everybody loves a latte.

05:33.071 --> 05:34.812
- Hey, um, thanks so much

05:34.856 --> 05:37.989
for putting absolutely
no thought into this.

05:38.033 --> 05:40.601
I have to get to work, so maybe
we could talk another time.

05:40.644 --> 05:44.082
- Hey, where are my pants?

05:48.086 --> 05:49.958
Hey.

05:50.872 --> 05:52.177
- Hey.

05:52.221 --> 05:54.354
- Hey.

05:54.397 --> 05:56.399
- I'm Noah.

05:56.443 --> 05:59.141
- He's my friend.

06:01.752 --> 06:04.973
- I've heard really great
things about you.

06:06.931 --> 06:08.759
- Um...

06:08.803 --> 06:10.239
you move fast.

06:10.282 --> 06:12.502
- I work with him.

06:12.546 --> 06:14.025
- Of course you do.

06:14.069 --> 06:15.418
- He's my boss.

06:15.462 --> 06:17.855
- Ah, of course he is.

06:17.899 --> 06:20.510
[shower running]

06:20.554 --> 06:24.079
Well, enjoy your lattes.

06:30.433 --> 06:33.610
[muffled chatter]

06:35.046 --> 06:37.179
- Next.

06:40.269 --> 06:41.531
- Hey, how you doing?

06:41.575 --> 06:44.055
- Well, look who it is.

06:44.099 --> 06:45.709
- Can we just do this?

06:45.753 --> 06:48.451
- I knew you'd be back.

06:48.495 --> 06:50.410
How much this time?

06:50.453 --> 06:52.020
- 35.
- Hundred?

06:52.063 --> 06:54.588
- Thousand.

06:56.546 --> 06:58.505
- Do I look like
a genie to you?

06:58.548 --> 06:59.897
- I've brought my pay stubs.

06:59.941 --> 07:01.246
- For $500.

07:01.290 --> 07:02.509
- So?

07:02.552 --> 07:03.945
- So you must be
tripping, girl.

07:03.988 --> 07:05.425
Your wish is denied.

07:05.468 --> 07:07.775
Next.

07:11.779 --> 07:14.129
- I am in real trouble, okay?

07:14.172 --> 07:16.087
- Well, you wouldn't be here
if you weren't.

07:16.131 --> 07:18.176
- I need to post bail.

07:18.220 --> 07:20.483
- Aww, bunny.
For who?

07:20.527 --> 07:22.572
- My husband.

07:22.616 --> 07:24.269
- Mm-hmm.

07:24.313 --> 07:25.923
- What's that?

07:25.967 --> 07:26.924
- What's what?

07:26.968 --> 07:28.883
- "Mm-hmm."

07:28.926 --> 07:31.189
- I'm just wondering
how it feels.

07:31.233 --> 07:32.669
- How what feels?

07:32.713 --> 07:35.629
- Being no better
than the rest of us.

07:36.543 --> 07:38.936
Next.

07:39.850 --> 07:41.286
- There's no security.

07:41.330 --> 07:43.419
It's basically just him,
the safe,

07:43.463 --> 07:45.595
and his bitch-ass judgment.

07:45.639 --> 07:48.163
- What if he recognizes you?

07:48.206 --> 07:50.513
- I'll drive getaway.

07:50.557 --> 07:51.949
- Isn't he behind glass?

07:51.993 --> 07:54.474
- We wait till it closes,
he comes out to lock up.

07:54.517 --> 07:57.564
You hold the gun,
B hits the safe.

07:57.607 --> 08:00.088
- We're gonna need new masks.

08:00.131 --> 08:01.045
- My treat.

08:01.089 --> 08:03.352
- Can I pick them?
- Sure.

08:03.395 --> 08:05.659
- Then I'm down.

08:08.836 --> 08:10.446
- I'm gonna lose my kids.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.666
- Stan is in a jail cell.

08:12.709 --> 08:14.972
- Because of us.
- I just need to get him out.

08:15.016 --> 08:17.497
- I know.

08:17.540 --> 08:20.978
- I mean, how else
am I gonna get the money?

08:24.242 --> 08:27.245
- I need 35 grand.

08:27.289 --> 08:29.030
- Yeah, I'm not Merril Lynch.

08:29.073 --> 08:30.771
- Well, then can I get
some fake cash

08:30.814 --> 08:32.250
so I can move cars?

08:32.294 --> 08:34.209
- [laughs]

08:34.252 --> 08:35.950
Uh, how's my cut coming?

08:35.993 --> 08:37.995
[moody pop music
playing through speakers]

08:38.039 --> 08:39.649
- Slow.
- And why's that?

08:39.693 --> 08:41.042
- You know why.

08:41.085 --> 08:43.392
- So those stoner kids
didn't feel bad

08:43.435 --> 08:44.611
and put all your money back?

08:44.654 --> 08:46.003
- You'll get your cut.

08:46.047 --> 08:48.310
- And when you do,
you'll get more money.

08:48.353 --> 08:49.572
That's how this all works.

08:49.616 --> 08:51.313
- You know what would be
so nice?

08:51.356 --> 08:52.357
- Hmm?

08:52.401 --> 08:53.924
- Is if you gave me a break

08:53.968 --> 08:55.360
just once.

08:55.404 --> 08:57.537
- Rough week?

08:57.580 --> 08:59.713
- My husband took my children.

08:59.756 --> 09:05.066
♪

09:10.506 --> 09:13.291
- I know it's lonely
at the top.

09:13.335 --> 09:15.337
- [scoffs]

09:19.733 --> 09:21.517
- Will you set her up for me.

09:21.561 --> 09:23.737
On my tab, please.

09:39.622 --> 09:42.059
- I'll have another.

09:43.583 --> 09:46.237
[knocking at door]

09:46.281 --> 09:52.113
♪

09:54.332 --> 09:55.899
- So here's the thing.

09:55.943 --> 09:57.640
- Are you trashed right now?

09:57.684 --> 10:00.600
- He's in jail because I'm not.

10:00.643 --> 10:02.689
- You are bombed.

10:05.779 --> 10:08.825
- So if we're gonna
do this thing,

10:08.869 --> 10:11.306
I would like
to choose the masks.

10:16.441 --> 10:17.791
- Okay.

10:19.401 --> 10:20.968
- And also, can I stay
the night here?

10:21.011 --> 10:24.275
Because it's really weird
without my kids.

10:26.713 --> 10:30.194
- It's really weird
without Stan, too.

10:30.238 --> 10:36.244
♪

10:38.681 --> 10:38.855
.

10:38.899 --> 10:41.292
- Only three
stuffed animals, all right?

10:41.336 --> 10:43.338
Last time your suitcase
looked like Noah's damn ark.

10:43.381 --> 10:47.124
Poor Grammy was picking up fuzz
for a week.

10:47.168 --> 10:49.561
Hustle.
She's making you spaghetti.

10:49.605 --> 10:51.999
- How's Daddy gonna eat?
- They'll feed him.

10:52.042 --> 10:53.870
- Where does he go
to the bathroom?

10:53.914 --> 10:55.437
- You know, in a bathroom.

10:55.480 --> 10:58.179
- There's a toilet in the cell.
- What's a cell?

10:58.222 --> 10:59.354
- Okay, you know what?

10:59.397 --> 11:00.790
Daddy's gonna come home
real soon.

11:00.834 --> 11:03.010
But right now
we gotta motor,

11:03.053 --> 11:05.055
or Grammy's gonna eat
all your spaghetti.

11:05.099 --> 11:06.230
- No!

11:06.274 --> 11:08.058
- Go get your animals then, go.

11:08.102 --> 11:11.540
And not that giant thing
you won at the fair.

11:13.760 --> 11:16.414
Go find your retainer, please.

11:17.589 --> 11:20.288
- Did he do it?

11:22.116 --> 11:24.205
- It's complicated.

11:24.248 --> 11:26.642
- Did he do
what they said he did?

11:37.044 --> 11:38.872
- Yes.

11:38.915 --> 11:41.701
- Then he should stay in jail.

11:48.751 --> 11:51.188
[knocking on door]

11:54.714 --> 11:56.716
both: Hey.
- Wanna do something?

11:56.759 --> 11:58.587
- Uh--
- Look, I know you're supposed

11:58.630 --> 12:01.459
to wait two days or whatever
to not seem like a psycho,

12:01.503 --> 12:05.202
but it's tomorrow in India
and I ordered a pizza.

12:05.246 --> 12:07.770
- To here?
- And wings.

12:07.814 --> 12:10.120
- Huh.
- Yeah, and then I felt gross,

12:10.164 --> 12:12.470
so I ordered a salad
and some green juice.

12:12.514 --> 12:13.689
- Wow.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.212
- And then I didn't want
to come off like one

12:15.256 --> 12:17.780
of those health nuts,
so I ordered Chinese.

12:17.824 --> 12:19.869
- Mm.
Well, I--

12:19.913 --> 12:21.915
I have to go do something
with my sister.

12:21.958 --> 12:25.309
Her husband left, so it's
kind of like a whole thing.

12:25.353 --> 12:26.746
- Oh.
I'd love to meet her.

12:26.789 --> 12:28.791
- You know, you--
you just met my ex.

12:28.835 --> 12:32.142
I feel like that's enough.
- Mm. That's a lot.

12:32.186 --> 12:33.274
- Okay, I tell you what.

12:33.317 --> 12:36.668
Why don't you stay here, okay?

12:36.712 --> 12:38.453
- Okay.
- Eat till you barf.

12:38.496 --> 12:40.803
I'll be back.
- Right.

12:51.858 --> 12:54.817
[quirky piano music]

12:54.861 --> 12:58.386
♪

12:58.429 --> 13:01.650
[woman singing
in foreign language]

13:01.693 --> 13:08.744
♪

13:33.943 --> 13:36.206
[microwave door shuts]

14:06.933 --> 14:08.804
- I'm starving.

14:08.848 --> 14:10.632
- Why do you even
eat those things?

14:10.675 --> 14:12.939
- They take three minutes
to heat in the microwave.

14:12.982 --> 14:15.202
- That's a plus?

14:15.245 --> 14:16.899
- They're ten for ten bucks
at Kroger.

14:16.943 --> 14:18.945
- Yeah, 'cause you gotta eat
like four of them

14:18.988 --> 14:20.381
to make one regular meal.

14:20.424 --> 14:21.730
- You know what else
is a lean cuisine?

14:21.773 --> 14:23.166
- Hmm?
- Ordering a Big Mac

14:23.210 --> 14:24.820
and taking one bite.
- Mm.

14:24.864 --> 14:28.128
Or having, like, three fries,
and it tastes way better.

14:28.171 --> 14:30.130
- Okay.
- Or one bite of pizza.

14:30.173 --> 14:31.392
- All the toppings you want.

14:31.435 --> 14:32.872
- Boom!
- Mm-hmm.

14:32.915 --> 14:35.309
We should market this.
- Why are we in crime?

14:35.352 --> 14:38.747
- You guys, 10:00.

14:38.790 --> 14:41.315
That's how you use
the clock thing, FYI.

14:41.358 --> 14:43.360
- [clicks tongue]

14:43.404 --> 14:44.579
- So cute.

14:44.622 --> 14:46.755
- I know.
I found cute colors.

14:46.798 --> 14:49.845
- I was gonna
tie-dye mine, but...

14:49.889 --> 14:51.760
[devious music]

14:51.803 --> 14:52.892
Don't move!

14:52.935 --> 14:54.023
- We're closed, y'all.

14:54.067 --> 14:55.764
- This'll be quick.

14:55.807 --> 14:57.592
- Come on!
- Go, move!

14:57.635 --> 14:59.768
- Okay, okay.
I'm moving, I'm moving.

14:59.811 --> 15:00.900
All right.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.553
- Hurry up!
- I'm moving, I'm moving.

15:02.597 --> 15:05.426
- Open the safe!
- I'm opening it.

15:05.469 --> 15:07.428
[safe beeping]

15:07.471 --> 15:09.473
- Come on!

15:09.517 --> 15:11.258
- It's not gonna open.

15:11.301 --> 15:13.608
- What do you mean?
- It's on a timer.

15:13.651 --> 15:15.610
It won't open again
till morning.

15:15.653 --> 15:16.872
- What?

15:16.916 --> 15:18.613
- I mean, I'm happy
to do this all night,

15:18.656 --> 15:20.963
but someone gonna see
your asses in the window

15:21.007 --> 15:23.835
and call the cops, so...

15:23.879 --> 15:25.576
- What do we do?

15:25.620 --> 15:28.188
- Why don't y'all just
come back in the morning?

15:28.231 --> 15:29.929
I'll bring the croissants.

15:40.591 --> 15:43.377
At some point,
I'm gonna need a burrito.

15:43.420 --> 15:45.988
And a big old cup
to urinate in.

15:51.994 --> 15:52.212
.

15:52.255 --> 15:53.865
- Oh, my God.
- It's the only way

15:53.909 --> 15:55.041
to get the money.

15:55.084 --> 15:56.433
- What else were
we supposed to do?

15:56.477 --> 15:57.826
- How about anything?

15:57.869 --> 15:59.436
- Oh, I'm sorry, should we have
left him there?

15:59.480 --> 16:01.525
- He would have had the cops
waiting with donuts

16:01.569 --> 16:02.874
when we came back.

16:02.918 --> 16:04.441
- Croissants, but...

16:04.485 --> 16:06.791
- I can't believe y'all
kidnapped a guy.

16:06.835 --> 16:07.967
Again.

16:08.010 --> 16:09.533
- He's like a baby bird,
you know?

16:09.577 --> 16:11.535
You--you can't touch it
